args: Wh-where am I? I can't see anything.\n...Ban-Ban? ...Anyone?
Eeek! Was that a beast's cry?!\nNo... I can't handle the thought of\nbecoming a beast and being alone...
Tiki! What a relief, you're awake.
Yes. And it was quite a nasty one,\nby the look of it.
Phew! Well, if it's just a dream\nthat means I'm going to be okay.
Are you SURE you'll be okay?\nYou don't look so hot.
I'm all right. I just haven't had\nmy scary dream in a while.
Yes. It's a dream where I'm alone and\nlost in a sea of endless darkness.
I hear the sounds of a beast and feel\nas if I'm about to become one myself.
Yes. It's like I'll end up becoming a beast\nand attack people. Maybe even kill them.
The dream is just so frightening,\nbut I haven't had it a while...
You're strained and nervous and stuck\nin a totally unknown new world.\nA nightmare isn't unexpected.
But so long as you're here in our world,\nI'll be sure to protect you.
It's okay now, Tiki. I'll protect you.
He said that to me, too.
Well, you did scream it out\nduring your nightmare.
Not at all. It sounds like he's a special\nperson to you; someone that you can\ntruly rely on in hard times.
He's all that and more!\nHis real name is Marth.
He helped me when I was all alone,\nand he woke me up when I was\nsleeping for such a long time!
He's the reason I have friends now.\nHe's the reason I'm not alone!
It is not unlike what my darling did.
Exactly. Oh, I put on a brave front about\nbeing on my own, but then he came along\nand melted my heart with his passion!
I suppose he might have saved me\nin that way...
So he's like your brother, then?
Mmm, he's more like my soul mate.\n...Eeee! I can't believe I said it out loud!
Well, it's the person that you were meant\nto be with. The one you SUPER like above\nand beyond anyone else in the world.
Oh, I'm the same. I SUPER like Mar-Mar!
Er, I think we might be using different\ndefinitions of the phrase ＂super like.＂
Well, when I think about my darling,\nI get an almost painful ache in my chest.
Ack! Are you having a cardiac event?!
What? No! ...Although I suppose it is a\nsort of sickness, in a manner of speaking.
This is terrible! We have to tell everyone!
Tiki, I'm fine. My heart may ache,\nbut it is a HAPPY ache.

When he and I are together, my heart
pounds and I feel an ache, but it also
makes me feel very happy and warm
on the inside.
I am filled to bursting with the strength\nto overcome anything for his sake!
So when I say I ＂like＂ my darling,\nthat is what I mean.
Yeah, I guess I don't understand.\nNot really, anyway.
But I DO understand what you mean\nwhen you say you could overcome\nanything for someone you care about!
That's why I want to get stronger\nand stronger for Mar-Mar!
And I'm sure you will, for you are\none of the bravest people I know.
Heh hee! Really? Thanks, Big Sis!
Still, I just wish Mar-Mar was here...
Tiki, would you like to take\na quick flight with me?
Yes! Let's both become dragons\nand soar through the night sky!
Wooow, that sounds like fun!\nEr, are you sure you have time?
Of course! Getting that kind of exercise\nis just the ticket for a good night's sleep.
I know you're full of unease right now,\nbut I promise that you WILL find a way\nback to your own world.
But as long as you're here, your big sis\nis going to make sure you enjoy it!
I'll take your worries and loneliness\nand punt them straight into the sun!
THERE'S the smile I wanted to see.\nNow let's take to the sky!
Yay! I super like you, Big Sis!
